'''Axel Koenders''' (born 28 September 1959) was one of the strongest [[triathlon]] competitors of the 1980s in the Netherlands. Besides numerous national titles, he won European championships in the long distance in 1987 and 1989.<ref name=r1/> In 1988 he set a world record at 8:13:11 in Roth, Germany. Besides triathlon he also competed in cycling and speedskating at the national level. Since 1994 Koenders runs his fitness center ''Axel Koenders Fit-Service''.<ref name=r2/>

Koenders graduated from the [[:nl:Academie voor Lichamelijke Opvoeding en Sport|Academy of Physical Education and Sport]] in Amsterdam, where he specialized in fencing, rowing and speedskating, and then for 10 years worked as a lecturer in physical education. Between 1997 and 2007 he was involved with the [[NOC*NSF|Dutch Olympic Committee]] and served as adviser at the 2000 Summer Olympics and 2002 and 2006 Winter Olympics.<ref name=r2/>

